====Welsh====
[[Welsh language|Welsh]] is traditionally divided into Northern and Southern dialects. In the north, some diphthongs may be short or long according to regular vowel length rules but in the south they are always short (see [[Welsh phonology]]). Southern dialects tend to simplify diphthongs in speech (e.g. ''gwaith'' {{IPA|/ɡwaiθ/}} is reduced to {{IPA|/ɡwaːθ/}}).
